            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Awarding Authority has established a framework agreement for capable suppliers to provide low carbon energy efficient infrastructure services, improvements and upgrades to existing or new facilities in the public sector in the UK. These upgrades should offer client public bodies guaranteed resilience valued through reduced running costs, reduced energy consumption and reduced carbon emissions. Proposals should guarantee minimum levels of savings over the period of each contract let under the framework which may be for 15 to 31 years long, or the life of the plant installed (if relevant). This framework agreement will be available for use by the entire UK public sector. Please see http://coch-cps.co.uk/our-services/ for a register of eligible users.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
