         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Eligible users of the framework agreement will be any or all public sector facilities in England, Wales, Scotland or Northern Ireland from any or all parts of the public sector including Ministry of Defence, education and further education, local authorities, unitary councils, city councils, and any of the greater city boroughs. In totality, any contracting authorities as defined in regulation 2 (1) of the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 including all explanatory notes thereto that are or become members of the Carbon and Energy Fund. A full list of eligible users of the proposed framework agreement is available at http://coch-cps.co.uk/our-services/our-frameworks/</P>
               <P>The framework is designed to work in parallel with the Salisbury NHS Foundation Trust Dynamic purchasing system (2016/S 156 283825) which is itself being amended to work with a wider range of technologies that can supplement CEF framework bids.</P>
               <P>All suppliers appointed to the framework agreement will be invited to participate in a mini-competition for each project. Normally three or four bidders will be taken forward into dialogue after scored interviews. Those shortlisted will be invited to enter into a dialogue, where, after the mini-competition will split into one of 2 routes. Routes refer to the way that suppliers will be asked to bid in the mini-competition, one of which will take multiple suppliers to a fixed price tender, and the other will reduce the suppliers down to one before seeking an investment grade proposal from that single supplier. The contract used for each project is based on the UK NHS standard contract. For this framework agreement, there are 2 forms of the contract, the adapted operating lease version and a new IFRIC 16 compliant version projects may be multi-site and may be a multi-agency (several public sector clients). Funding for projects may come by way of grants, funding by the Participating authority, funding arranged by the CEF, or funding procured by the bidder or any mix of the above.</P>
               <P>Mini-competitions will be conducted in accordance with the process detailed in the invitation to tender document. The framework will be available for use by all public bodies in the UK, as listed in the ITT that are or become members of the Carbon and Energy Fund.</P>
